summary: In this context, 2-methoxy-2-methylpropane and 3-xylene are both mentioned as volatile organic compounds (VOCs) that may be present in the air of high-rise apartments. However, there is no direct discussion of their relationship, interactions, or specific relevance to each other beyond their classification as VOCs. The study focuses on measuring various VOC concentrations without detailing how these two compounds might relate to one another.
